<item>
            <title>[OAK-2259] SegmentBlob equals check should verify compaction in both directions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2259</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like the SegmentNodeState checks compaction in one direction &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, while the SegmentBlob checks in the other direction. This will not break anything as the fallback is to use byte comparison, but it will be terribly slow.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m proposing to verify both directions in the #equals check, to make sure we don&apos;t miss out.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/trunk/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/plugins/segment/SegmentNodeState.java#L401&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/trunk/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/plugins/segment/SegmentNodeState.java#L401&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/trunk/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/plugins/segment/SegmentBlob.java#L198&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/trunk/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/plugins/segment/SegmentBlob.java#L198&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
